<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="353" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War/9–1244:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador to the Greek Government in Exile</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Cairo</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-12T20:00:00-04:00">September 12, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>92. Reurtel 305, September 12. Department has no objection to
                                Moshanov’s departure for Ankara.</p>
                            <p>For your information the Soviet Government has proposed that the
                                Bulgarian terms be presented either at Moscow or at Ankara. We are
                                indicating a preference for Ankara, but are not yet informed <pb facs="0427" n="415" xml:id="pg_415"/> of the British views. We
                                are also agreeing to having the EAC review the terms and examine
                                certain as yet undisclosed “amendments and additions” which the
                                Russians wish to propose.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>